# YouTube MP4 Downloader (Next.js)

**Quick**: Paste a YouTube link on the homepage and click **Download MP4**.

## Setup (local)
1. Clone repo
2. `npm install`
3. `npm run dev`
4. Visit `http://localhost:3000`

## Deploy to Vercel
1. Push this repo to GitHub.
2. Go to vercel.com → Import Project → Select your GitHub repo.
3. Use defaults. Vercel will install dependencies and deploy.

**Warning about Vercel:** Vercel serverless functions are subject to execution time & memory limits. Downloading large videos may fail. If you get truncated downloads, consider deploying the API to Railway, Render, or a small VPS that supports long-running processes.

## Legal & Responsible Use
Only download videos you own or have explicit permission to download. Do not use this app to infringe copyright or circumvent access restrictions.

